      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For the pain, you need to take ibuprofen at the maximum recommended dose, which is usually 800mg every 6 to 8 hours, but you should definitely check the bottle for the absolute limit. Pain when bearing weight is a sign of a significant issue, but it doesn't automatically mean a break; it could be a severe ligament tear. Honestly, if you can't put *any* weight on it, you should be more concerned about a fracture and get it professionally X-rayed today.",
